description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_keys.c
Lines: 790-796

When decoding PUT payload, non-string value types are skipped incorrectly:
```c
} else {
    /* Skip other types */
    continue;
}
```

This 'continue' skips to the next map iteration WITHOUT advancing 'pos' past the value. The parser position stays at the value byte, causing the next key decode to read garbage.

Example: if payload contains {"extra": 42, "pubkey": "..."}, the integer 42 is not skipped properly, corrupting subsequent parsing.

Should call a zcbor_any_skip equivalent or manually advance pos based on the CBOR type.

Category: CORRECTNESS - parsing logic error
